description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Working in partnership with our service partners, at Luton and Dunstable Hospital&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;An opportunity exists for a Specimen Reception Assistant (SRA) to join the team of dedicated enthusiastic staff in the Blood Sciences Department at &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bedford Hospital&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;. The post is for a Specimen Reception Assistant who will assist the department in providing an analytical service to the Trust and community.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The department is housed in a state of the art purpose built Pathology Block with excellent staff and training facilities. The department is-equiped with all new equipment using Beckman Coulter, Werfern and Griffol analysers.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The department is an IBMS pre and post HCPC registration training laboratory.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Every encouragement will be given with participation in Continual Personal Development through onsite training and attendance at suitable external events alongside gaining valuable experience working in a busy routine Blood Sciences Department. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Support will be offered to suitably qualified and enthusiastic staff wishing to further their career.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful applicant will be required to work 22.5 hrs per week, some weekend/extended day working will be required.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sharon Mucha - Specimen Reception Manager sharon.mucha@bedfordhospital.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
